What I'm really revealing is what an idiot I was to miss that.

@Thanksverymuch

Apartment living, pest control is already paid for, so I can ask them to come out anytime, fortunately.

Fire ants were NOT fun, but no allergic reaction, just the itchy burning feeling that lasted for days and didn't get much better with diphenhydramine or hydrocortisone. I'll skip on those, thank you.

@Dom D

You've never even knew about rebuses, and you solved a puzzle with one?

Hats off!

@B

I am genuinely in awe of you both, and anyone else who accomplished the same trick.  Absolutely no sarcasm or reservations.

That is thinking outside the box at a level I can only dream of.

@Briana
I skied, once, in the Cairngorms, Scotland, 1968. Cord trousers, shirt, wool jumper, jacket, woollen gloves, woollen hat, 2 pairs socks and stout leather boots tied onto wooden skies with laces. 
I was ill with the cold and never did it again!

