@Steve 

True. I've seen this in puzzles before, though. A lot of people don't know the distinction and just use both words to indicate any variation of a given color.  It's another example of words losing their precise definition for a less specific one due to people assuming a meaning from context, and if you object to it you get accused of being pedantic.

I did the mental shrug.

