@Jack McCullough
My fave Estado is Quintana Roo, because the name is so adorable, but it never fits.....

Hand up for ROUT and GIANT.

@Steve

I used to feel this way too. But once I started doing more and more of them, I found that I enjoyed them. Now, when I realize the puzzle is a rebus, I look forward to figuring it out. 

And it clearly takes an enormous amount of skill and creativity to create one, just like it does with all crossword puzzles. Give them a chance and you might learn to love them as I have.

@Jørn Earl Otte
What a great reply, and an equally great example, too.
Thank you.

@Steve L

They're specifically requesting more non-rebus submissions now for Thursday. Look it up.

It may take some time for that to take effect.

@greyeyes

Maybe you're in the majority, maybe not. Those that don't like rebus puzzles tend to be vehemently and bitterly opposed, though, which makes for squeakier, more-grease-demanding wheels.

I like them, a lot of other people do too, the only place I know of where they're regularly available is here, and there's endless other places to find more traditional crosswords. As noted, there  will probably be fewer of them in the future. Isn't that enough?

@Helen Wright
I couldn't find any vAA reference for the UK, only CAA. Can you educate me?
I love your livestock adventures, but I'll settle for pheromones today. I use a product called Delta Dust for the nasty little biters that try to gain entry. I apply that around the outside foundation to discourage the climbers. We also have little families of geckos that dine on the ants. They are very well fed. Cheers!

@CCNY
