These EpiPens are expensive!  And you still have to go to the ER, which is ALSO expensive, esp if you waited too long and have to take an ambulance...  Plus they keep you way longer than you want to stay.

@Mean Old Lady

I've (unfortunately) also had some experience with fire ants that invaded my apartment down here. Fortunately, ant venom is not one of my allergies, so I just had the itchy burning sensation on multiple bites for a few days after that. Not much fun for anybody, let alone people our age.

Had the pest control people out and that took care of that invasion, but it's Florida, so it's a continuing battle.

@JayTee
Same here--and I stay alert.  Just that ONE fire ant made it past my defenses and gloves and got to my forearm...  I did not know fire ants are related to wasps! 
There are also "native black Mississippi fire ants" which swarm at you (but no mounds, so no warning)...the stings burn incredibly, then itch awfully, and last for about 3 months before healing...  Hope they don't make it to FLorida!

@Sue Plantinga
