@Nicholas Sinisi
The NYT suggests how to accomplish his in their FAQ and daily write-ups. You should see an icon resembling a pencil on the keyboard, that'll allow multiple letters per square.
I think Deb explains how using a single "t," (I believe) will suffice in today's .

@Nicholas Sinisi

Since you said "more than two letters," I assume you understand how to enter a rebus, but you just find three letters or more a little unwieldy on a phone screen.

You can enter all three letters (or more, when this occurs), which will be illegible on a regular phone screen, of course, but then you can pinch the screen out.  You'll only see the section of the puzzle in question, but you can pinch back in when you want to.

@Nicholas Sinisi
I encourage you to read Deb's 3d or 4th paragraph in Today's Theme, for a mini tutorial of the rebus. She provides the link.
My keyboard, on second look, has a tab labeled "rebus." Check yours and let us know.

@Katie

I really resist herbicides and pesticides, but there are times when everything else you've tried has failed.

My issue was with a yard full of Creeping Charlie.  And my wife has no mercy on wasps.  I don't either, really, unless there's only one or two and them I can something get them out of my living space without killing them.

@Ian

